Sydney Wamalwa - Personal Resume Website

Welcome to my personal resume website! This project showcases my skills, experience, education, and projects in a clean, responsive, and interactive format. It is built using **HTML**, **CSS**, and **JavaScript**, and is designed to be mobile-friendly and easy to navigate.

Live Demo

You can view the live version of this website here:  
[Live Demo on GitHub Pages](https://wamalwasydney.github.io/resume)

Features

- Responsive Design**: The website adapts seamlessly to desktop, tablet, and mobile screens.
- Interactive Elements**: Includes a responsive navbar, hover effects, and a contact form with validation.
- Professional Layout**: Clean and modern design with clear sections for About, Experience, Education, Projects, and Contact.
- Custom CSS**: Styled without using any frameworks like Bootstrap.
- Deployed on GitHub Pages**: Easily accessible and shareable.

Technologies Used

- **HTML5**: For structuring the content.
- **CSS3**: For styling and responsiveness.
- **JavaScript**: For interactivity (e.g., form validation).
- **Git & GitHub**: For version control and deployment.

Project Structure
resume/
├── index.html # Main HTML file
├── styles.css # Custom CSS file
├── script.js # JavaScript file for interactivity
├── assets/ # Folder for images and icons
│ ├── profile.jpg # Profile picture
│ ├── project1.png # Project screenshots
│ └── project2.png
└── README.md # This file


How to Run Locally

1. **Clone the Repository**:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/WamalwaSydney/resume.git
   cd resume

    Open the Project:

        Open the index.html file in your browser to view the website.

    Modify the Content:

        Edit the index.html, styles.css, and script.js files to customize the website for your own use.

Deployment

This project is deployed using GitHub Pages. To deploy your own version:

    Fork this repository.

    Go to your repository settings and enable GitHub Pages.

    Select the main branch as the source.

    Your site will be live at https://<username>.github.io/resume.

